<subSubSection id="C361651AFF80B370FF6B4B3CFCB3FD04" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC43691FF80B370FF6B4B3CFAA3FDAF" blockId="98.[151,1436,151,719]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FF80B370FF6B4B3CFEEAFDD7" bold="true" box="[199,315,516,540]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species occurs in two forms. The macropterous form (November–December) is more robust, larger and darker and has fully developed hind wings. The brachypterous form (July collections) has lobe-like short hind wings, incapable of flight. The species breeds on 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FF80B370FD554B74FC09FDAF" box="[761,984,588,612]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Achyranthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspera">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FF80B370FD554B74FC09FDAF" box="[761,984,588,612]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Achyranthes aspera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FF80B370FBAA4B74FB69FDAF" box="[1030,1208,588,612]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Amaranthaceae</taxonomicName>
) on Nandi Hills.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC43691FF80B370FF6B4B49FCB3FD04" blockId="98.[151,1436,151,719]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FF80B370FF6B4B49FEB0FD43" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[199,353,624,648]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nandiensis">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FF80B370FF6B4B49FEB0FD43" box="[199,353,624,648]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">N. nandiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FF80B370FE4D4B49FD92FD4C" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[481,579,624,648]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matai">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FF80B370FE4D4B49FD92FD4C" box="[481,579,624,648]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">N. matai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in the structure of the male genitalia especially in the structure of the anal collar process and aedeagus. The illustration of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FF80B370FC044BACFB1DFD67" authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1916" box="[936,1228,660,684]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="campbelli">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FF80B370FC044BACFBA3FD67" box="[936,1138,660,684]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Agallia campbelli</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B60FF80B370FB554BACFF15FD04" author="Distant, W. L." pageId="98" pageNumber="99" refId="ref72045" refString="Distant, W. L. (1916) Rhynchota. Homoptera, Appendix. In: Shipley, A. E. &amp; Marshall, G. A. K (eds) The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Volume VI, viii + 248 pp. Taylor &amp; Francis, London." type="book" year="1916">Distant (1916: 230</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13402A14FF80B370FF634B8FFEFCFD04" box="[207,301,695,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–172" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1579,1602]" captionTargetBox="[272,1315,207,1541]" captionTargetId="figure-97@39.[259,1326,189,1559]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 165–172. Species of Dryodurgades: 165–169. Dryodurgades formosana (Matsumura): 165. Male pygofer and anal collar, lateral view; 166. Connective, anterior view; 167. Style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 168. Aedeagal apex, posterior view; 170–172. Dryodurgades lamellaris Vilbaste: Aedeagus, lateral view; 171. Aedeagus, anterior view; 172. Style dorsal view." pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Fig. 168</figureCitation>
) refers to the macropterous female of this species.
</paragraph>
